Under the [[EU Common Agricultural Policy]], subsidies known as '''headage payments''' are paid to producers based on the number of head of a specific type of [[livestock]]. Such [[payment]]s may be contingent upon participation in a supply control program (e.g., limiting the number of livestock on a [[farm]]).

