{{ref improve|date=January 2013}} {{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Ministry of National Defence |nativename = ''Ministerium für Nationale Verteidigung'' |logo = DDR Verteidigungsminister Kfz-Flagge.svg |logo_width = 150px |logo_caption = Flag of the Ministry of National Defence |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |picture = |picture_width = 225 |picture_caption = |formed = 1 March 1956 |date1 = |date1_name = |date2 = |date2_name = |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |dissolved = 23 April 1990 |superseding = |jurisdiction = {{flagicon|East Germany}} [[National People's Army]] |headquarters = [[Strausberg]] |latd = |latm = |lats = |latNS = |longd = |longm = |longs = |longEW = |employees = |budget = |chief1_name = |chief1_position = |chief2_name = |chief2_position = |chief3_name = |chief3_position = |parent_agency = |child1_agency = |child2_agency = |website = |footnotes = |chief4_name=|chief4_position=|chief5_name=|chief5_position=|chief6_name=|chief6_position=|chief7_name=|chief7_position=|chief8_name=|chief8_position=|chief9_name=|chief9_position=|parent_department=}}
The '''Ministry of National Defense''' ([[German language|German]]: ''Ministerium für Nationale Verteidigung - MfNV'') was the chief administrative arm of the East German [[National People's Army]]. The MND was modeled on the [[Ministry of Defense (Soviet Union)|Ministry of Defense]] of the [[Soviet Union]]. The headquarters of the Ministry was in [[Strausberg]] near [[East Berlin]]. The [[Guard Regiment Hugo Eberlein]] provided security and guard services to the Ministry. The Ministry also had its own publishing house, [[Military publishing house of the German Democratic Republic]].
==Minister of Defence== The NVA was administered through the Ministry of National Defense, one of the principal branches of the national government. The ministers of National Defense were: {{Officeholder table start | showorder = y | showimage = y | officeholder_title = Minister of Defence | showtermlenght = y | showelection = n | showaltofficeholder = y | alt_officeholder_title = [[Council of Ministers of the GDR|Chairman]] | party_col = 1 }} {{Officeholder table | order2 = 1 | image = Bundesarchiv Bild 183-1986-0617-024, Willi Stoph.jpg | military_rank = ''[[Army general (East Germany)|Armeegeneral]]'' | officeholder = [[Willi Stoph]] | officeholder_sort = Stoph, Willi | born_year = 1914 | died_year = 1999 | died = | term_start = 1 March 1956 | term_end = 14 July 1960 | timeinoffice = {{ayd|1956|03|01|1960|07|14}} | alt_party = Socialist Unity Party of Germany | alt_officeholder = [[Otto Grotewohl|Grotewohl]] }} {{Officeholder table | order2 = 2 | image = Bundesarchiv Bild 183-1982-1217-023, Heinz Hoffmann.jpg | military_rank = ''Armeegeneral'' | officeholder = [[Heinz Hoffmann]] | officeholder_sort = Hoffmann, Heinz | born_year = 1910 | died_year = 1985 | died = y | term_start = 14 July 1960 | term_end = 2 December 1985 | timeinoffice = {{ayd|1960|07|14|1985|12|02}} | alt_party = Socialist Unity Party of Germany | alt_officeholder = [[Otto Grotewohl]] | alt_officeholder2 = [[Willi Stoph]] | alt_officeholder3 = [[Horst Sindermann]] | alt_officeholder4 = [[Willi Stoph]] }} {{Officeholder table | order2 = 3 | image = Bundesarchiv Bild 183-1988-0704-410, Heinz Keßler.jpg | military_rank = ''Armeegeneral'' | officeholder = [[Heinz Kessler]] | officeholder_sort = Kessler, Heinz | born_year = 1920 | died_year = 2017 | died = | term_start = 3 December 1985 | term_end = 18 November 1989 | timeinoffice = {{ayd|1985|12|02|1989|11|18}} | alt_party = Socialist Unity Party of Germany | alt_officeholder = [[Willi Stoph]] | alt_officeholder2 = [[Hans Modrow]] }} {{Officeholder t