The Air Force / Air Defense Command ({{lang-de|Kommando Luftstreitkräfte&Luftverteidigung}}) ('''LSK / LV''') was created in 1956 for government air force and air defense. A year later, the administrations for the joint command LSK / LV-based Eggersdorf was established. It was led by the Chief of the Air Force Command / Air Defense ({{lang-de|Chefs des Kommandos Luftstreitkräfte/Luftverteidigung}}).
