The '''Swedish Research Council''' ({{lang-sv|Vetenskapsrådet}}) is a [[Government agencies in Sweden|Government agency in Sweden]] established in 2001, with the responsibility to support and develop [[research|basic scientific research]]. Its objective is for Sweden to be a leading nation in scientific research. The agency has three main functions: *To distribute government funding for basic research *To advise the government on issues related to scientific research *To educate the general public about scientific research
==See also== * [[Open access in Sweden]]
