'''Voroshylovskyi District''' ({{lang-uk|Ворошиловський район}}) is an urban district of [[Donetsk]], [[Ukraine]], named after [[Marshal of the Soviet Union]] [[Kliment Voroshilov|Kliment Yefremovich Voroshilov]].
It is the Donetsk's downtown and was created in 1973 after splitting away from the [[Kalininskyi District, Donetsk]].
